text: I fell in love with this idea that you
could actually build a bot that does
what Warren Buffett does which is read
financial statements so I built it and
then I built a start-up around that I
went from in undergrad when I did my
internships and when I interned and
worked in the summer I was working with
people who are very professional and
prided themselves on being professional
when I went to Windows if you didn't
have Pizza stains on your shirt you were
considered overdressed so it was a big
culture shock for me the most important
thing I built was the Grameen foundation
had their tech ops here in Seattle and I
volunteered there and I actually built a
test framework for them so they could
test some of their banking software
whether you were trying to go mobile and
when they were trying to bring software
to the process for the loans for women
in the federal third world tech is
changing and people are finally waking
up and so there is a real opportunity
there
